The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Sitapur, Aug. 16 (PTI): An FIR has been lodged against more than 5,000 people in Sitapur, Uttar Pradesh, including village heads and panchayat officers, for allegedly swindling funds meant for a pension scheme.          inquiry found 5,055 people had posed as pensioners. The scam has affected residents in 117 villages and Rs 91 lakh was drawn in the name of the fake pensioners, police said.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Delhi government has directed all educational institutes to install fire extinguishers and make the school buildings fire-proof within six months in view of a recent Supreme Court order.                  
	 Khargone (PTI): A former branch manager of the State Bank of India was arrested on Sunday in Khargone, Madhya Pradesh, for allegedly withdrawing Rs 28 lakh by creating a fake account about a year back. Pushpendra Naik was on the run ever since the matter came to light, superintendent of police Pramod Varma said.                   
	 Dhar (PTI): Three persons, of them two schoolchildren, were killed and 32 injured when a bus carrying them plunged into a valley near Mandu in Dhar, Madhya Pradesh, on Sunday. The third victim was a teacher of the school. The injured have been admitted to a nearby hospital.                   
	 Valsad (PTI): One person was killed and four were injured when they suffered an electric shock while erecting a pole in a railway station shed in Valsad, Gujarat. The incident occurred when the iron pole touched a live wire. Abdul Aziz Pathan died on the spot.                  
	 Mehsana (PTI): A man arrested in connection with a theft has allegedly died in a police lock-up near Mehsana, Gujarat. Yogesh Choudhary was arrested in the case a day before he was found dead, the police said. The reason behind the death is not known and the body has been sent for a post-mortem, they added.                                                                                                                           
